sample.title: Why young grads are struggling to find jobs
sample.description:

"Right now is a really difficult time to find a job," Cory Stahle, senior economist at Indeed Hiring Lab, told CNBC.

sample.title: Why beef prices are out of control in the U.S.
sample.description:

sample.title: Troops in eastern Ukraine speak to the BBC | BBC News
sample.description:
Ukraine insists it is still resisting Russian advances in the city of Pokrovsk in the eastern part of the country.
 
This comes despite Russian claims last week that it had taken control of the entire city. 
 
Pokrovsk has been a key battleground for more than a year, and Ukraine sees it as a major obstacle to preventing Russian forces from taking control of the entire Donetsk Region. 
 
The BBC‚Äôs Defence Correspondent Jonathan BEALE has been talking to Ukrainian troops who are still defending the city.

sample.title: Sudan air force bombing kills at least 1,700 civilians, investigation says | BBC News
sample.description:
Sudan's air force has carried out bombings in which at least 1,700 civilians have died in attacks on residential neighbourhoods, markets, schools and camps for displaced people, according to an investigation into air raids in the country's civil war.

The Sudan Witness Project says it has compiled the largest known dataset of military airstrikes in the conflict, which began in April 2023.
 
Its analysis indicates that the air force has used unguided bombs in populated areas.
 
The Sudanese Armed Forces did not respond to a BBC request for a comment.

But it has previously denied allegations of targeting civilians, saying its air strikes are "directed solely" at its rival paramilitary Rapid Support Forces "gatherings, location and bases recognised as legitimate targets".

sample.title: Australian PM's message to under-16s ahead of social media ban. #Australia #BBCNews
Australia's social media ban for children has left big tech scrambling | BBC News
sample.description:
Australia is banning social media for children under the age of 16 from December 10. 

Under-16s will no longer be allowed to have social media accounts, including X, Instagram and TikTok, all existing profiles must be deactivated, and they will not be able to set up new accounts. 

The Australian government says the ban - a world-first policy popular with many parents - is aimed at protecting children from harmful content and other risks such as cyberbullying and grooming. 

Some young campaigners have argued the ban disregards the rights of children.

And social media platforms have argued the ban will be ineffective, difficult to implement, could isolate vulnerable teenagers and drive others into dark corners of the internet

sample.title: Thailand and Cambodia launch fresh strikes in ongoing border dispute | BBC News
sample.description:
Tensions between Thailand and Cambodia have once again exploded along their shared border, derailing a fragile ceasefire backed by US President Donald Trump.
 
At least three Thai soldiers and seven Cambodian civilians have been killed since Monday, with the countries accusing one another of starting the violence.
 
The clashes, which have also seen Thailand launch air strikes along the border, are the most serious since the ceasefire was agreed in July.
 
Trump has called on both sides to respect the agreement, news agency Reuters said.
